---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Mealmoji Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-800">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">
      Mealmoji Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="italic text-gray-500 mb-6">Last Updated: June 2026</p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Mealmoji is a food-diary app that lets you photograph your meals, cut the
      food out into stickers, log them to a calendar, and optionally get AI
      calorie and macro estimates. This policy explains what data the app uses
      and when. We designed Mealmoji to keep your meals on your device by
      default; a few optional features involve other services, and those are
      described clearly below.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Information We Collect
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Mealmoji has no account and no sign-in. We do not ask for your name, email,
      or any personal profile. Your meal content — photos, generated stickers,
      captions, calorie/macro figures, dates, and your settings — is created and
      stored on your device.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      On-Device Sticker Cutout
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Turning your photo into a sticker uses Apple's Vision framework and runs
      entirely on your device. The cutout step does not send your photo anywhere.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      AI Calorie &amp; Macro Analysis (optional)
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Calorie analysis is optional and only happens when you tap "Analyze" on a
      meal. When you do, that meal photo is sent over a secure connection to our
      analysis service, which uses Google's Gemini model to estimate the dish,
      calories, and macronutrients, and returns the result to the app. The image
      is used only to produce that estimate; we do not use it to identify you,
      build an advertising profile, or sell it. If you never tap "Analyze," your
      photos are not sent off your device for analysis.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      iCloud Sync (optional)
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      If you enable iCloud sync, your meal diary and images are stored in your
      own private iCloud account using Apple's CloudKit so they back up and sync
      across your devices. This data lives in your iCloud account, governed by
      Apple's privacy policy; we cannot access it. Sync is off by default.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Apple Health (optional)
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      If you turn on Apple Health, Mealmoji writes the calories and macros of the
      meals you log into the Health app, with your permission. Mealmoji only
      writes this data — it does not read any health data — and this information
      is not sent to us or any third party.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Advertising</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The free version shows ads through Google AdMob. To serve ads, the Google
      Mobile Ads SDK may collect device and usage information and identifiers, as
      described in
      <a
        href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Google's Privacy &amp; Terms</a
      >. You can limit ad tracking in iOS Settings, and Premium subscribers see
      no ads at all.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Subscriptions &amp; Purchases
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Mealmoji Premium is sold through Apple's In-App Purchase. Payments are
      processed by Apple; we never receive your payment-card details. Apple may
      share aggregate, non-identifying purchase information with us.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Permissions</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Camera</strong> — to take photos of your meals in the app.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Photo Library</strong> — only when you import an existing photo.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Notifications</strong> — only if you enable meal reminders.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Apple Health</strong> — only if you enable writing meals to
        Health.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Permissions are requested only when needed, and the app does not use your
      camera or photos in the background.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Third-Party Services
    </h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Google</strong> — the Gemini model (calorie analysis, only when
        you tap "Analyze") and Google AdMob (ads in the free version).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Apple</strong> — iCloud/CloudKit (optional sync), In-App Purchase
        (subscriptions), and HealthKit (optional).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Children's Privacy
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Mealmoji is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
      collect personal information from them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Your Choices</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      You control your data. Delete individual meals at any time, and deleting
      the app removes the meals and photos stored on your device. You can turn
      iCloud sync, Apple Health, and reminders on or off in Settings, and manage
      or cancel your subscription anytime in your Apple Account settings.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">
      Changes to This Policy
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The "Last Updated"
      date above reflects the latest version.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">
      Questions about this policy? Email
      <a
        href="mailto:getvisiblelondon@gmail.com"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">getvisiblelondon@gmail.com</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-500">— Mealmoji</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
